<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-65-1020 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author discusses the implications to Canada if the cruise missileis tested and deployed. The author says that the Soviet Union would havelittle incentive to restrain the size of its own arsenal if the cruisemissile were stockpiled, ready for rapid deployment. For Canada, thedanger of cooperating in the testing and development of the cruise missileis the danger of abandoning all efforts to control the spiralling accumulationof weapons of mass destruction. The author presents the pros and consof Canada allowing the testing of the cruise missile in its country andof Canada refusing permission to test the weapon.</TEXT></DOC>